    "enDesc": "The Guide for the Perplexed, written by Maimonides (Rambam), contains the author’s philosophical views. It is written in the form of a letter to his student, Rabbi Joseph ben Judah of Ceuta. Originally written in Judeo-Arabic, it was later translated to Hebrew (1204). The Guide includes Rambam’s objection to anthropomorphism, an explanation of the Biblical account of creation, and a description of the Merkavah.",
    "enShortDesc": "Maimonides’ 12th-century philosophical masterwork, written as a letter to his student demonstrating the compatibility of Judaism and philosophy.",
    "heShortDesc": "יצירת המופת של הרמב\"ם שנכתבה במאה ה-12 כאיגרת לתלמידיו שבה הוא מצביע על ההתאמה בין עיקרי היהדות ובין הפילוסופיה.",
